Help Type: topic
Topic: command

Command Reference

Archive-first commands:
  create      Create an archive from source material at source stage.
  estimate    Estimate words, token scale, calls, time, cost, and risk before queueing graph or summary jobs.
  status      Show archive readiness and object counts.
  index       Show the archive home/index page.
  list        List archive objects with filters, stable order, and cursor paging.
  find        Find objects by whitespace-separated keyword discovery.
  grep        Search objects for one exact continuous text phrase.
  page        Open one detailed object page by id.
  read        Print one object as continuous plain text.
  links       Show outgoing node links.
  backlinks   Show incoming node links.
  related     Show graph-adjacent knowledge units.
  path        Find a directed graph path between two nodes in one chapter.
  pack        Pack deterministic context around a known object id.
  export      Export a projection from the archive.

Queue commands:
  queue add      Create a graph or summary job for one archive chapter.
  queue list     Show active jobs by default; use --all for historical jobs.
  queue status   Show one job snapshot.
  queue watch    Stream job events; use --jsonl for agent-friendly output.
  queue pause    Stop scheduling a job while preserving its workspace.
  queue resume   Return a paused job to the queue.
  queue cancel   Mark a job canceled and preserve its workspace for debugging.
  queue boost    Move a queued job to the front without preempting running jobs.
  queue target   Change graph/summary target within allowed boundaries.
  queue clean    Remove old terminal job records and workspaces.

Command shapes:
  spinedigest create <archive.sdpub> [source] [--input-format <format>]
  spinedigest estimate <archive.sdpub> [--stage <source|graph|summary>] [--json]
  spinedigest queue add <archive.sdpub> --chapter <id> [--to graph|summary] [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  spinedigest queue list [--all] [--active] [--input <archive.sdpub>]
  spinedigest queue watch <job-id> [--jsonl] [--from beginning|now]
  spinedigest status <archive.sdpub> [--json]
  spinedigest index <archive.sdpub> [--json]
  spinedigest list <archive.sdpub> --type <types> [--id <ids>] [--chapter <ids>] [--order <doc-asc|doc-desc>] [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json]
  spinedigest find <archive.sdpub> <query> --type <types> [--match <any|all>] [--chapter <ids>] [--order <doc-asc|doc-desc>] [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json]
  spinedigest grep <archive.sdpub> <query> --type <types> [--chapter <ids>] [--order <doc-asc|doc-desc>] [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json]
  spinedigest page <archive.sdpub> <selector> [--json]
  spinedigest read <archive.sdpub> <selector>
  spinedigest related <archive.sdpub> --node <id> [--json]
  spinedigest pack <archive.sdpub> <selector> [--budget <chars>] [--json]
  spinedigest export <archive.sdpub> --output-format <format> [--output <path>]

Direct transform:
  spinedigest transform [--input <path>] [--output <path>] [--input-format <format>] [--output-format <format>] [--digest-dir <path>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>] [--stage <planned|source|graph|summary>] [--verbose]

Maintenance:
  spinedigest meta <archive.sdpub> [metadata options] [--json]
  spinedigest cover <archive.sdpub>
  spinedigest chapter <action> <archive.sdpub> [options]
  spinedigest config status [--llm <json>]
  `chapter tree` without `apply` is read-only structure inspection; mutating chapter actions are maintenance.

